{
  "texts": [
    "An ML workflow is a high-level overview of the different steps needed for an ML project.",
    "It consists of three main steps: the data curation, where a dataset is acquired; the learning data preparation, where the dataset is transformed into a proper format ready to be processed by the ML algorithm; and the learning process, where the ML algorithm is trained on the dataset, and is evaluated afterwards.",
    "We provide https://app.dimensions.ai/discover/publication \"Eye Tracking\" OR \"Eye-Tracking\" OR \"Eyetracking\" (\"Eye Tracking\" OR \"Eye-Tracking\" OR \"Eyetracking\") AND (\"Deep Learning\" OR \"Machine Learning\" OR \"Neural Network*\" OR \"Decision Tree*\" OR \"SVM\" OR \"Support Vector\" OR \"LSTM\" OR \"CNN\" OR \"Random Forest*\" OR \"KNN\" OR \"MLP\" OR \"LDA\" OR \"Cluster*\" OR \"Unsupervised Learning\" OR \"PCA\").",
    "a comprehensive overview of how ML has been used in scanpath analysis for passive gaze-based interaction to highlight research gaps that could benefit from further investigation; we do so by providing answers to these questions:",
    "What research domains have used machine learning to analyze scanpaths, and what passive gaze-based learning tasks have they focused on?"
  ]
